26/08/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Russian police have arrested a Bosnian Serb who is wanted by the UN war crimes tribunal, BiH media reported Thursday (25 August). 
According to unconfirmed reports, Dragan Zelenovic, 44, was detained Wednesday on the basis of an international arrest warrant issued by The Hague tribunal. 
Zelenovic is charged with crimes against humanity and violations of the laws or customs of war for his alleged role in the detention, torture and sexual assault, including rape, of Bosnian Muslim women and girls in the town of Foca in 1992-1993. 
(RTS, Moscow Times, Dnevni avaz, Nezavisne novine - 26/08/05; AFP, Reuters, B92, Fena, RTRS - 25/08/05)
